milestone.title: Docs Only
milestone.description:
Documentation only pull requests and issues can go in here.

This is a place to put PRs that are purely updating the documentation - i.e. no code changes.

When triaging I was putting such PRs into the next milestone, which at the moment would be 1.2.2 but I found that since these doc-fixes were not blocking releases, it was hiding how much real work was needed before the milestone was ready for the release.  

In effect, I created a parallel track for documentation updates.  Then when I had the time, I could sit down and knock off a dozen of these PRs at my leisure.

title: fix(angular-mocks): use copy of mock data in $httpBackend
body:
fix(angular-mocks): use copy of mock data in $httpBackend

Copy mock data returned from the mock $httpBackend.
This prevents modifications to the response from affecting future responses.
Previously, this misbehavior was being mitigated by the deep copy in $resource, but that no longer exists.

https://github.com/angular/angular.js/issues/5265

title: chore(CHANGELOG): introduce perf() section for performance-related commits
body:
Instead of using fix() or chore() when labelling a commit which improves
speed or performance use perf(). Perf commits will be listed in the
CHANGELOG under "Performance Improvements".

For example:
perf($animate): cache all getComputedStyle operations to reduce additional reflows

title: chore($resource): Use shallow copy instead of angular.copy
body:
Replace calls to angular.copy with calls to a new function, shallowClearAndCopy.
Add calls to copy for cache access in $http in order to prevent modification of cached data.
Results in a measurable improvement to the startup time of complex apps within Google.

title: refactor($parse): clean up evaled function
body:
refactor($parse): clean up evaled function

Remove unused variables from the created function.
Use == null instead of (=== null || === undefined)
Don't wrap the evaled function in a closure when not unwrapping promises.
This change also brings a slight performance improvement: http://jsperf.com/optimizing-parse

title: chore(Angular.js): Use call and === instead of apply and ==
body:
chore(Angular.js): Use call and === instead of apply and == in type check functions

Updates isDate et al to use call instead of apply and === instead of ==.
The change to call brings minor performance improvement and === is just better practice than ==.
http://jsperf.com/call-vs-apply-tostring

title: fix(input): prevent double $digest when using jQuery trigger.
body:
If an event was performed natively, jQuery sets the isTrigger property.
When triggering event manually, the field is not present. Manually
triggered events are performed synchronously which causes the "$digest
already in progress" error.

title: chore(Scope): short-circuit after dirty-checking last dirty watcher
body:
Stop dirty-checking during $digest after the last dirty watcher has been re-checked.
This prevents unneeded re-checking of the remaining watchers (They were already checked in the previous iteration), bringing a substantial performance improvement to the average case run time of $digest.

Closes #5272
